Sometimes it’s okay to be a little EXTRA. 

When @iamdawnmccoy asks you to come out to Palm Springs for a day with your daughter and to play and take photos… you just say YES. 

When she says to put on a Vera Wang gown… you just say yes. 

… and when she tells you to grab the @cahomeanddesign magazine that features you and your work as one of The Voices Of Tomorrow (can’t wait to show you!)… you just say yes. 

Thank you Dawn for giving us space to celebrate ourselves (and Happy Birthday to you ❤️). 

Photo: @andrewcabral_photography @DawnMcCoyMedia
Dress: @VeraWang at @SummerColonyLivingPalmDesert on @ShopElPaseo
Location: @CocoCabanaPS luxury vacation rental home in Palm Springs

Well I teased it yesterday in my big ‘ol ball gown… but today I am so honored to present new work in The @cahomeanddesign Voices Of Tomorrow issue. 

Thank you @theshookones , @astoneink , and @zekeruelas for your beautiful words and photos, @cjisrad for styling, and to all of my amazing vendors. 

This was a very special project for me for a very special family, so to be included as a “Voice Of Tomorrow” means the world. Be prepared for an influx of photos 😉. #murphydeesigned •

Today I will be cooking a stew in my new @ourplace pot my mom gave me (green of course)… and “stewing over” my thoughts and goals for the new year. 

I don’t like to overthink the New Year, or to define it as some big “end or beginning of”. Isn’t that a bit overwhelming? 

I’d rather embrace it as a continuation of all of the work I’ve done… professionally, personally, emotionally, and physically… each and every day. 

So here I am, in the present moment, setting intentions and feeling immense gratitude.

Thank you for being here and supporting me as you do… I can’t wait to keep creating and hopefully to keep inspiring you in this space and more! #homesweetdeesign #murphydeesigned •

Avery Asked me yesterday… “Mama, are you sad we are getting older?”. 

On the contrary my love! 

I told her that not only I am I so grateful to spend every day, aging, with her… I actually LOVE this stage of their life. 

Except for the for the non-stop sibling arguing and emerging pre-teen attitudes, I can honestly say I enjoy this time even more than when they were babies. I love the conversations. I love the questions. I love the goofiness. I love the bonding and laughter over more adult-type subjects. I love watching their talents emerge and take shape. I love the independent streaks followed by absolute vulnerability. I love their changing faces. In a baby obsessed world… I love their “tweenage” magic ✨. 

Maybe I am just hanging on for dear life before they become actual teenagers, and we get a whole new level of arguments and attitudes… but I’m hoping (I know) I will find the magic in those things too. 📷 by @maxwanger
